  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">While holding at least pound of applicable material, you touch the targeted object, which can also be currently held or worn by another creature.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\"> </span>If the creature is not willing, you need to make a spell attack roll. You can only use precious material and grades that are equal to your level or lower.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">For the next hour, the target object’s material turns into the material used as a reagent, acquiring all its relevant properties. This spell does not make a perfect transition of the material; it merely changes the item so that it utilizes material properties appropriate to the type of equipment and its temporary material, if any.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><strong>Heightened (6</strong></span><sup><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><strong>th</strong></span></sup><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><strong>) </strong>The duration of the spell becomes 8 hours.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><strong>Heightened (8</strong></span><sup><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><strong>th</strong></span></sup><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><strong>)</strong> The range of the spell becomes 30 feet, and you can affect up to 5 applicable targets within range within one casting of this spell.</span></p>"
